        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 2 at 4:18PM PDT by NWS Medford OR</headline>
        <description>At 417 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lava Beds National Monument, or 38 miles southeast of Klamath Falls,
moving east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lava Beds National Monument and Tionesta.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
